Project: MERN E-Commerce Site (v1.0)
1. ğŸ“– Project Overview
This document outlines the technical architecture for a lightweight, MERN-stack e-commerce application. The system allows users to browse a list of products, view details for a specific product, and manage a shopping cart.

The application is built with a decoupled architecture:

Backend: A Node.js/Express API responsible for database operations and serving product data.

Frontend: A React single-page application (SPA) that provides a clean, responsive UI and handles all user interaction and state.

2. âš™ï¸ Technology Stack
Category	Technology	Purpose
Backend	Node.js	JavaScript runtime environment for the server.
Express.js	Server framework for building the REST API.
Mongoose	Object Data Modeler (ODM) for MongoDB.
CORS	Middleware to enable Cross-Origin Resource Sharing.
Dotenv	Module to manage environment variables.
Frontend	React.js	Library for building the user interface.
React Router DOM	Client-side routing for page navigation.
Axios	HTTP client for making requests to the backend API.
Database	MongoDB Atlas	Cloud-hosted NoSQL database.
State	React Context API	Global state management for the shopping cart.

