4. ğŸš€ Installation & Setup
Prerequisites
Node.js (v16 or later)

NPM (comes with Node.js)

A MongoDB Atlas account and a connection string.

A. Backend Setup
Navigate to the backend directory:

Bash

cd backend
Install dependencies:

Bash

npm install
Create a .env file in the backend root. This is critical.

Code snippet

MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster...
PORT=5000
Replace the MONGO_URI value with your own MongoDB Atlas connection string.

B. Frontend Setup
Open a new terminal and navigate to the frontend directory:

Bash

cd frontend
Install dependencies:

Bash

npm install
5. ğŸ’¾ Database Seeding
To populate your database with the provided dummy data:

Ensure your .env file in the backend is correct.

Run the seeder script from the backend directory:

Bash

# This DELETES all existing products and adds the new ones
node seeder.js -import
To clear the database, you can run:

Bash

node seeder.js -destroy
6. ğŸ Running the Application
You must run both servers simultaneously in two separate terminals.

Terminal 1 (Backend):

Bash

cd backend
node server.js
Output: Server is running on port: 5000

Terminal 2 (Frontend):

Bash

cd frontend
npm start
This will open the app in your browser at http://localhost:3000.

7. ğŸ”Œ API Endpoints
The backend serves a REST API at http://localhost:5000/api.

Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/api/products	Retrieves a list of all products.
GET	/api/products/:id	Retrieves a single product by its MongoDB _id.

Export to Sheets

8. âš›ï¸ Frontend Architecture
Pages
HomePage.js: Fetches all products from /api/products and displays them in a grid using the Product component.

ProductPage.js: Fetches a single product using the URL parameter (:id) and displays its details.

CartPage.js: Displays all items currently in the CartContext.

State Management (CartContext.js)
Global state management for the cart is handled via React's Context API to avoid "prop drilling."

CartProvider: A wrapper component (in index.js) that holds the cart state.

State: cartItems (Array of product objects with a quantity property).

Functions:

addToCart(product): Adds a product to the cartItems array. If the item already exists, it increments the quantity.

removeFromCart(productId): Removes a product from the cartItems array by its ID.

Usage: Components access the cart state by using the useContext(CartContext) hook.
